        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "b7aa632a-9512-4ba8-898b-c50bbd1fe81b",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Phishing"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1566"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "RansomHub affiliates use phishing as an initial access vector, delivering deceptive emails that impersonate trusted entities — including business partners, financial institutions, and IT service providers — to lure victims into interacting with malicious content. Phishing enables both credential harvesting and direct malware delivery, providing the foothold needed to authenticate to external remote services or execute tooling on victim hosts. The technique branches into two delivery sub-techniques: malicious attachments (T1566.001) that execute loaders or droppers upon opening, and malicious links (T1566.002) that redirect victims to credential-harvesting portals or payload-staging infrastructure. Phishing complements RansomHub's other initial access vectors and is used selectively against targets where exposed services or exploitable vulnerabilities are not available."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_start",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_end",
                    null
                ]
            ],
