        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "d31656d6-0f83-4319-91c5-ecdde4c0f5f2",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Valid Accounts"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1078"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "Valid credentials are the most consistently observed initial access vector in RansomHub intrusions, with domain accounts (T1078.002, Reports count: 3) being the primary sub-technique alongside local accounts (T1078.003). Credentials are sourced from initial access brokers operating in underground markets, prior phishing campaigns that harvested corporate SSO or VPN credentials, or credential stuffing attacks against exposed authentication endpoints. Once obtained, valid credentials allow RansomHub affiliates to authenticate directly to VPN gateways, RDP endpoints, and cloud management consoles without triggering exploit-based detection, providing a stealthy authenticated foothold that mirrors legitimate administrator behavior. Valid accounts are also reused across persistence (T1078.002 x3), privilege escalation, and defense evasion phases throughout the intrusion lifecycle."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_start",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_end",
                    null
                ]
            ],
            "anchors": {
