        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "28a55f7c-cfd6-47d0-b32f-a52ed698aba3",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Exploit Public-Facing Application"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1190"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "RansomHub affiliates exploit vulnerabilities in internet-exposed applications and services to gain unauthenticated initial access without requiring victim interaction. Targeted platforms include VPN appliances, web application frameworks, and enterprise software with known unpatched CVEs. Exploitation provides a shell or reverse beacon on the externally exposed system, which serves as a staging platform for internal reconnaissance, credential dumping, and lateral movement prior to ransomware deployment. RansomHub's exploitation capability reflects its recruitment of experienced affiliates with access to both public and private exploit tooling, enabling the group to target organizations that have hardened against phishing but maintain unpatched external attack surfaces."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_start",
                    null
                ],
                [
                    "execution_end",
                    null
                ]
            ],
            "anchors": {
